## Limitations

The findings are based on available online resources and may not capture the full spectrum of religious influences on public policy globally. Additionally, the data is primarily focused on the United States, which may not be representative of other cultural or national contexts. Further research could explore comparative studies across different countries to provide a more comprehensive understanding of religion's role in public policy.